# Craftify Templates Marketplace - Windsurf Project Rules

## Project Overview
Craftify Templates Marketplace is a monorepo e-commerce application for buying and selling digital templates with user authentication, reviews, ratings, wishlist management, and Stripe payment integration.

## Tech Stack
- **Frontend Framework**: Next.js 14+ with App Router and TypeScript
- **Backend Framework**: Express.js with Node.js
- **Database**: MongoDB with Mongoose ODM
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS with custom design system
- **State Management**: Zustand (cartStore, authStore)
- **Data Fetching**: React Query (@tanstack/react-query)
- **Forms**: React Hook Form
- **Icons**: Lucide React
- **Animations**: Framer Motion
- **Payment**: Stripe integration
- **Package Manager**: pnpm (monorepo workspace)

## Monorepo Structure
```
craftify-templates-marketplac/
├── apps/
│   ├── api/          # Express.js backend (port 3001)
│   └── website/      # Next.js frontend (port 3000)
├── packages/         # Shared packages
└── package.json      # Root workspace config
```

## Frontend File Structure (apps/website/src/)
- `app/` - Next.js App Router pages and layouts
- `components/` - Reusable UI components
- `components/ui/` - Base UI components (Button, Input, Toast, etc.)
- `components/navigation/` - Navigation components (Navbar, Footer)
- `lib/` - Utilities, API clients, types, helpers
- `hooks/` - Custom React hooks organized by domain
- `types/` - TypeScript type definitions

## Backend File Structure (apps/api/)
- `controllers/` - Route controllers with business logic
- `models/` - Mongoose models with validation
- `routes/` - Express route definitions
- `middlewares/` - Custom middleware (auth, validation)
- `services/` - External service integrations (Stripe)
- `utils/` - Helper functions and serializers

## Code Style
- Use functional components with hooks (frontend)
- Use async/await for async operations
- Keep components small and focused (single responsibility)
- Use TypeScript for type safety
- Follow existing naming conventions (camelCase for variables, PascalCase for components)
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Write clean, maintainable code

## API Integration
- Frontend uses `api.ts` in `lib/` for all API calls
- Backend uses Express.js with middleware for authentication
- Store auth tokens in cookies (authCookies)
- Use React Query for data fetching and caching
- Handle errors gracefully with user-friendly messages
- Follow RESTful API patterns
- Use JWT tokens for authentication

## Styling Guidelines
- Use Tailwind CSS for all styling
- Follow the purple-indigo-cyan gradient theme
- Use glassmorphism effects (backdrop-blur, transparency)
- Ensure responsive design (mobile-first approach)
- Use Framer Motion for smooth animations
- Maintain consistent spacing and typography
- Custom scrollbars matching brand identity

## Key Features
- User authentication with JWT
- Template browsing and search with pagination
- Wishlist management
- Reviews and ratings system (1-5 stars)
- Shopping cart functionality
- Stripe payment integration with webhooks
- Order management and tracking
- Creator profiles

## Design System
- **Primary Colors**: Purple (#9333ea), Indigo (#6366f1), Cyan (#06b6d4)
- **Effects**: Glassmorphism, backdrop-blur, gradients
- **Typography**: Clean, modern sans-serif
- **Spacing**: Consistent scale (4px base unit)
- **Border Radius**: Rounded corners (rounded-3xl for cards)

## Git Workflow
- Write clear, descriptive commit messages
- Use conventional commit format (feat:, fix:, refactor:)
- Keep commits atomic and focused
- Test changes before committing
- Follow project-specific commit message patterns

## Development Notes
- Backend runs on port 3001
- Frontend runs on port 3000
- Use pnpm for package management in monorepo
- Restart backend server after adding new routes
- Frontend uses API client at `lib/api.ts`
- Backend routes are in `apps/api/routes/`
